        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Sometimes you need the form to be printed or forwarded.\r\nThis can be direct by the printer or an email f.x.\r\n\r\nBut there you don't need the whole form elements anymore, only the labels and the value which is set to the form elements.\r\n\r\nSo my suggestion is a method, that don't render the form with the whole <input>, <select>, <textarea>,...elements.\r\nOnly one HTML tag is used for the label and the value (for formatting).\r\n\r\nHow it could look like (tags from \"default\" zend form settings):\r\n{code}\r\nMethod: echo $form->renderPrinted();\r\n<dl class=\"zend_form\">\r\n<fieldset>\r\n<legend>Title<\/legend>\r\n\r\n<dt>Title<\/dt>\r\n<dd>myTitleValueFromForm<\/dd>\r\n\r\n<dt>Text<\/dt>\r\n<dd>test text...<\/dd>\r\n\r\n...\r\n{code}"
        },
