                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44299",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\r\nYour HTML-Code is wrong and why is this a major issue?\r\n\r\nCompare with: HTML_QuickForm::freeze()\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nWhat is wrong with the HTML-Code? :-)\r\nIt's an extract and not the complete HTML.\r\n\r\nThe type is not an issue, it's submitted as an improvement. But you are right with the priority.\r\n\r\nYes, \"HTML_QuickForm::freeze()\" is exactly what this method should do.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-07T01:46:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-07T01:46:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44300",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Martin,\r\nlook here:\r\n{code}\r\n<dl class=\"zend_form\">\r\n<fieldset>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI think, this issue depends on ZF-10205",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-07T02:00:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-07T02:00:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44301",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That issue is similar, but exactly the same.\r\n\r\nWhen you want to send the form as an information e-mail, the form part (input, select, ...) are still in the source?\r\nIf i understood that solution correct.\r\n\r\n\r\nThat HTML part was generated with Zend_Form. When this form is wrong, there is maybe an issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-07T02:35:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-07T02:35:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44302",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To \"freeze\" a form, you need a element-decorator which produces plain text.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-07T03:27:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-07T03:27:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45590",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\r\nThat HTML part was generated with Zend_Form. When this form is wrong, there is maybe an issue.\r\n{quote}\r\nThis not an error. It is your incorrect definition.\r\n\r\n{code:title=Example with standard decorators}\r\n\/\/ Form\r\n$form = new Zend_Form();\r\n\r\n\/\/ Elements\r\n$form->addElement(\r\n    'text',\r\n    'foo',\r\n    array(\r\n        'label' => 'Foo',\r\n    )\r\n);\r\n\r\n$form->addElement(\r\n    'text',\r\n    'bar',\r\n    array(\r\n        'label' => 'Bar',\r\n    )\r\n);\r\n\r\n$form->addElement(\r\n    'submit',\r\n    'send',\r\n    array(\r\n        'label' => 'Send',\r\n    )\r\n);\r\n\r\n\/\/ Display group\r\n$form->addDisplayGroup(array('foo', 'bar'), 'baz');\r\n\r\n\/\/ View\r\n$view = new Zend_View();\r\n$view->setEncoding('utf-8');\r\n$view->doctype(Zend_View_Helper_Doctype::XHTML1_STRICT);\r\n\r\necho $form->render($view)\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code:title=Output|borderStyle=solid}\r\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"\" enctype=\"application\/x-www-form-urlencoded\">\r\n    <dl class=\"zend_form\">\r\n        <dt id=\"baz-label\">&#160;<\/dt>\r\n        <dd id=\"baz-element\">\r\n            <fieldset id=\"fieldset-baz\">\r\n                <dl>\r\n                    <dt id=\"foo-label\">\r\n                        <label for=\"foo\" class=\"optional\">Foo<\/label>\r\n                    <\/dt>\r\n                    <dd id=\"foo-element\">\r\n                        <input type=\"text\" name=\"foo\" id=\"foo\" value=\"\" \/>\r\n                    <\/dd>\r\n                    <dt id=\"bar-label\">\r\n                        <label for=\"bar\" class=\"optional\">Bar<\/label>\r\n                    <\/dt>\r\n                    <dd id=\"bar-element\">\r\n                        <input type=\"text\" name=\"bar\" id=\"bar\" value=\"\" \/>\r\n                    <\/dd>\r\n                <\/dl>\r\n            <\/fieldset>\r\n        <\/dd>\r\n        <dt id=\"send-label\">&#160;<\/dt>\r\n        <dd id=\"send-element\">\r\n            <input type=\"submit\" name=\"send\" id=\"send\" value=\"Send\" \/>\r\n        <\/dd>\r\n    <\/dl>\r\n<\/form>\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
